{"id":2503,"date":"2021-03-02T11:00:43","date_gmt":"2021-03-02T09:00:43","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/154.0.202.153\/?page_id=2503"},"modified":"2024-04-27T10:56:07","modified_gmt":"2024-04-27T08:56:07","slug":"standing-committee-on-public-accounts","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-public-accounts\/","title":{"rendered":"Standing Committee on Public Accounts"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Mandate&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675569668-f3928061-8287&#8243;][vc_column_text]The Committee has the duty to assist and act on matters referred to it by the House for scrutiny and to submit reports on:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>The accounts showing the appropriation of the sums granted by Parliament to meet public expenditure of the Republic;<\/li>\n<li>Such other accounts and any other matter or task as my be referred to the Committee by the House or under any other law;<\/li>\n<li>All reports of the Auditor General on any such accounts;<\/li>\n<li>All accounts and reports of accounts where the State has interests; and<\/li>\n<li>All State-Owned Enterprises and Parastatals.<\/li>\n<li>The Committee reports on its findings and makes its recommendations to the Assembly for consideration and debate.<\/li>\n<li>Upon adoption of the reports and recommendations by the Assembly, the Committee has a duty to report on the implementation of the recommendations as adopted.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;O\/M\/A Served&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675569691-b44a1c73-5801&#8243;][vc_column_text]All O\/M\/As Accounts[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Clerks&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675589127-7d28d971-b2df&#8221;]<style type=\"text\/css\" data-type=\"the7_shortcodes-inline-css\">.dt-team-shortcode.team-masonry-shortcode-id-6aaa5c6fe3196295d26a3ce2214b8a76 .team-desc {\n  padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px;\n}\n.dt